      "content": "so you're saying the systemic bias side is more \"supported\" by the actual evidence then? it feels like the \"deterrence\" argument is just something people use to justify keeping things the way they are, even if it's not actually working. do you think it's even possible to have \"tough on crime\" policies that aren't inherently biased?",
